f=\r\nounded Divine Life Society, among other &quot;actions&quot;! :-) &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div al=\r\nign=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;\n size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/=\r\nfont&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; siz=\r\ne=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000=\r\n000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;f=\r\nont color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;If he established DLS wit=\r\nh the expectation that it becomes a success or 10,000 people join it or som=\r\ne such thing, then it would become an ignorant action, i.e. action with att=\r\nachment. If he did the action completely ready for any outcome and without =\r\na sense of ownership, and as an instrument of the divine will, then it is n=\r\neither &quot;worldly&quot; nor binding nor ignorant. The problem is not &quot;actions&quot;, bu=\r\nt actions with attachment and a sense of ownership, i.e. actions driven by =\r\nthe will and agenda of a limited ego. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;fon=\r\nt color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div\n a=\r\nlign=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;Actions s=\r\nhould not be spoken ill of like this. Detached action is a *sacred duty* of=\r\n every being. Gods and rishis came back again and again to earth to engage =\r\nin detached action. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000=\r\n&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font=\r\n color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;=\r\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nb=\r\nsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdan=\r\na&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;If &quot;the atman is entirely opposed to action&quot;, then why is atm=\r\nan (Self) even allowing action? Why doesn&#39;t it simply halt everything? Or, =\r\nis all the action happening outside of atman? Is there anything outside of =\r\natman at all? &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=\r\n=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp;\n &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font colo=\r\nr=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;Some buddhist philosophies coined=\r\n the term anatman (non-Self) to describe transient things. But, in Vedic ph=\r\nilosophy, there is no anatman. All that is is atman (Self). Ocean is perman=\r\nent and still, but ripples that arise in it are transient and moving. But r=\r\nipples are part of ocean only and you do not start labeling ripples as &quot;non=\r\n-ocean&quot;. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;V=\r\nerdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#=\r\n000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;Atman or Purusha or Shiva is the potent=\r\nial energy of this cosmos, while Maya or Prakriti or Shakti is the kinetic =\r\nenergy of this cosmos. Shiva and Shakti are seen as different entities by s=\r\nome people, but rishis have declared their oneness. Potential energy become=\r\ns kinetic energy and vice versa. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font col=\r\nor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp;\n &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\r\n=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;Atman is the =\r\nstill ocean and Maya is the force (kinetic) that gives rise to moving rippl=\r\nes on the surface. A ripple that exerts itself to move in a particular way =\r\nkeeps colliding with the force and keeps moving hither and tither in a chao=\r\ntic way for a very long time. A ripple that does not exert itself and moves=\r\n smoothly as dictated by the force will eventually grind to a halt and ceas=\r\ne to exist as a ripple on the surface. It then becomes part of the still oc=\r\nean. If a ripple exerts itself to become still, it may even take longer to =\r\nbecome still. What prolongs a ripple is not movement but resisting the dire=\r\nction given by the force and exerting to move in a particular way (or even =\r\nexerting to become still). A ripple that surrenders to the force will ride =\r\nthe course and die down faster. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font colo=\r\nr=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp;\n &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\r\n=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;Contemplate t=\r\nhe imagery I presented above regarding Atman and Maya, ignorant/egoistic ac=\r\ntion and detached action! It is very apt. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;=\r\n&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;di=\r\nv align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;*&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp; * &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;V=\r\nerdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#=\r\n000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;In not-so-distant past, sannyasins rema=\r\nined in ashrams and isolated themselves from society and did their sadhana.=\r\n Swami Vivekananda started a new trend. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;f=\r\nont color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div =\r\nalign=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;A sannya=\r\nsin renounces expectation\n of things from people stuck in transient materia=\r\nl world and does not depend on anyone. But he may still *give* basic materi=\r\nal things to those hapless people stuck in transient material world! For ex=\r\nample, Swami Vivekananda and his brother monks went to places struck by pla=\r\ngue, floods, droughts, cyclones etc and served people. They provided food, =\r\nmedicines etc (instead of lecturing that body is a transient illusion and o=\r\nne should stop worrying about its welfare!) and also did construction work.=\r\n They ignored the welfare of their own bodies, put themselves at risk and o=\r\nvercame maya personally. But they served those still stuck in maya without =\r\nlooking down upon them or their needs or maya that trapped them! Those who =\r\nwanted food got food, those who wanted medicines got medicines and those wh=\r\no wanted books got books. Renunciation means you do not expect anything fro=\r\nm anyone and accept whatever comes to you naturally. It does not necessaril=\r\ny mean rejecting or\n ignoring others. Overcoming maya does not require beli=\r\nttling maya or belittling those still stuck in maya. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div alig=\r\nn=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/fon=\r\nt&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=\r\n=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;The trend started by Swami Vivekananda was continued by Swami Sivana=\r\nnda. For that reason, it is a bit weird to see him talking so ill of action=\r\n! He was obviously trying to inspire a specific group of people for a speci=\r\nfic body of work. These words are neither universal nor do they reflect his=\r\n tremendous wisdom I have seen elsewhere! &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;=\r\n&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;di=\r\nv align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;*&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp; * &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;V=\r\nerdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div\n align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;=\r\n#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;All this intellectual discussion may b=\r\ne satisfying to some, but the quote from Swami Brahmanananda in the other m=\r\nail is very apt: &quot;You have been only hearing of all these spiritual things.=\r\n Now realise them. You have done enough study and reasoning. Now do some sp=\r\niritual practice. First take up that aspect of God which appeals to you mos=\r\nt. Follow your own path of Sadhana. When you realise God through it, you wi=\r\nll feel the joy of realising Him also in other aspects and through other pa=\r\nths.&quot; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verd=\r\nana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000=\r\n000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;According to Ramakrishna, Swami Brahmanand=\r\na was a gopala who accompanied Lord Krishna in a previous life. His words a=\r\nre simple, pragmatic and powerful. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font c=\r\nolor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div\n alig=\r\nn=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;I want this =\r\nforum to facilitate exchange of Vedic knowledge (and I will also be contrib=\r\nuting, though in spurts). But I want more that this forum should inspire pe=\r\nople to do sadhana and find God. In the end, that is what matters. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;=\r\n/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2=\r\n&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;V=\r\nerdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;Best regards, &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font col=\r\nor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;Narasimha &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div alig=\r\nn=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;------------=\r\n------------------------------------------------------- &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div a=\r\nlign=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font col